l be only <b>in English/Hindi language.</b><br /><br />13. Please read the Instruction Sheet carefully, then click on <b>&quot;I HAVE READ THE INSTRUCTIONS&quot;.</b><br /><br />14. You will be required to go through a <b>SAMPLE TEST</b> before you access the <b>Main Exam</b>.<br /><br />15. You are requested to <b>avoid touching</b> the wires and cables as it could lead to the <b>computer</b> shutting down.<br /><br />16. In case you face <b>any technical issue while logging into the examination or during the exam,</b> please contact the Test Administrator immediately to address the issue. <b>DO NOT DISCUSS THE ISSUE WITH ANY CANDIDATES SITTING NEXT TO YOU. Discussing any matter with others in the examination hall shall be deemed to be resorting to adoption of unfair means in the examination.</b><br /><br /><b>17. Please make sure you sign in the space provided against your details in the Attendance Sheet. Signing on the Attendance Sheet is mandatory, and your candidature will be considered null &amp; void without it.<br /><br />18. All candidates have to mandatory sit for 60 minutes, from the start of the examination. NO CANDIDATES WILL BE ALLOWED TO LEAVE THE EXAMINATION HALL BEFORE THE LAPSE OF 60 MINUTES FROM THE START OF THE MAIN EXAMINATION.<br /><br />19. In Case candidates go to the washroom , attendance should again be taken for such candidates.</b><br /><br />20. In case a Differently Abled candidate is scheduled at a centre, then he/she will get extra 20 minutes per hour. That means, for such a candidate, total test duration will be 2 hours(2.00 HRS + 40 Min). This extra time will automatically reflect in the exam timer of such candidates` question paper.<br /><br /><u><b>About Question Paper</b></u><br /><br />1)The Question Paper consists of multiple choice objective type questions with 4 options out of which only 1 is correct and new question type &quot;Questions without answer&quot; i.e. After the question text, a response box will be provided for keying in the answers. No options will be provided and hence, the candidate will have to key- in the response for each such question.<br /><br /><div>2)&quot;Questions without answer&quot;will be numerical in nature. The candidate will be required to key in numbers (0 to 9) along with + or - signs as per question requirement.</div><div><br /></div><div>a)Candidate will be required to use `Virtual keyboard` in-built into the system to key in the numbers /sign.</div><div><br /></div><div>b)In case the candidate has to provide the answer in decimals, he/she will have to key in the required number of digits after the decimal (.) sign, as specified in the question.</div><div><br /></div><div>c)Candidate can key-in only numbers, +/- signs or (.) decimal point. No alphabet and other character/s like coma (,) or hyphen (-) will be accepted.</div><div><br /></div><div>d)After keying-in the response, the candidate will have to save the answer by clicking the &quot;Save&quot; button before moving to next question.</div><div><br /></div><div>e)If the candidate does not click on the &quot;Save&quot; button, the response keyed-in by the candidate will not be saved and consequently, marks will not be awarded.</div><div><br /></div><div>f)In case candidate has made any entries in the `answer box` (question without option cases) than without saving or erasing the entered numbers, the candidate cannot move to next question. For this purpose candidate will be shown alert (&quot;Click Save or Clear Response&quot;)to save the entries.</div><div><br /></div><div><div><b><u>Guidelines for answering Questions without options:</u></b></div><div><br /></div><div>i.Some questions of this type will be administered in all the above mentioned subjects. The questions will be diverse and will cover some/all the modules in the subject.</div><div><br /></div><div>ii.Each such question will carry `One mark` like other questions.</div><div><br /></div><div>iii.These questions will not be in the MCQ form