t<br /><br />a) After submitting of the question paper provisional score card / result will be displayed on the computer screen.<br />b) Candidate can download provisional score card from the web site by 3 to 4 days from institute`s web site.<br /><br />7. Candidates are not allowed to write anything even any questions / options in either side of the Admit Card, if it found doing so , he/she shall be deemed to be resorting to adoption of unfair means in the examination.<br /><br />8. Examination venue will not make any arrangement for safe keep of Mobile Phone, electronic /smart gadgets, bag, or any valuable items.<br /></b><br />9. After completion of frisking , candidates are requested to move to the REGISTRATION DESK, registration desk operator will capture photo and system generated random seat number will be generated the same Seat Number &amp; Lab Number must be written in space provided in the admit card along with <b>VERIFIED </b>seal put in front of respective examination date in the admit card.<br /><br /><div style=\"text-align: justify;\">10. Candidates would be provided with rough sheet for rough work at the exam centre. The rough sheet should be returned to the invigilators before leaving the exam hall/lab.</div><br />11. On the Computer Screen available in front of you, you are required to type your <b>Membership no. &amp; PASSWORD</b> as printed on your Admit Card.<br /><br />12. Please verify your details in the screen, the exams will be only <b>in English/Hindi language.</b><br /><br />13. Please read the Instruction Sheet carefully, then click on <b>&quot;I HAVE READ THE INSTRUCTIONS&quot;.</b><br /><br />14. You will be required to go through a <b>SAMPLE TEST</b> before you access the <b>Main Exam</b>.<br /><br />15. You are requested to <b>avoid touching</b> the wires and cables as it could lead to the <b>computer</b> shutting down.<br /><br />16. In case you face <b>any technical issue while logging into the examination or during the exam,</b> 