acter/s like coma (,) or hyphen (-) will be accepted.</div><div><br /></div><div>d)After keying-in the response, the candidate will have to save the answer by clicking the &quot;Save&quot; button before moving to next question.</div><div><br /></div><div>e)If the candidate does not click on the &quot;Save&quot; button, the response keyed-in by the candidate will not be saved and consequently, marks will not be awarded.</div><div><br /></div><div>f)In case candidate has made any entries in the `answer box` (question without option cases) than without saving or erasing the entered numbers, the candidate cannot move to next question. For this purpose candidate will be shown alert (&quot;Click Save or Clear Response&quot;)to save the entries.</div><div><br /></div><div><div><b><u>Guidelines for answering Questions without options:</u></b></div><div><br /></div><div>i.Some questions of this type will be administered in all the above mentioned subjects. The questions will be diverse and will cover some/all the modules in the subject.</div><div><br /></div><div>ii.Each such question will carry `One mark` like other questions.</div><div><br /></div><div>iii.These questions will not be in the MCQ format i.e. no answer options will be provided.</div><div><br /></div><div>iv.After every question, a response box will be provided for keying in the answers.</div><div><br /></div><div>v.The candidate will have to key-in the response for each of such questions.</div><div><br /></div><div>vi.Candidate will be required to only use `Virtual keyboard` in-built into the system to key in the numbers /sign.</div><div><br /></div><div>vii.These questions will be numerical in nature/have numerals as the answer. The candidate will be required to key in numbers (0 to 9) along with appropriate prefix. If answer is negative, it should be preceded by `-` sign.</div><div><br /></div><div>viii.The `-` sign wherever applicable should precede the number. For example, if the correct answer is -27, in